Ombudsman
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an officer of Parliament appointed by the Legislature to investigate complaints by individuals against the state or public services. [Swedish, legal representative]
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
